## Problem Statement

Despite high demand for Uber rides (6,745 trip requests), only 41.97% of trips are successfully completed, leaving nearly 58% of requests unfulfilled.  
The unfulfilled trips are driven by two major issues:

- Driver availability gaps (39.29% of requests fail due to “No Cars Available”)  
- High cancellation rates (18.74% of requests cancelled by drivers or riders)  

This supply-demand imbalance is most severe during peak hours (18:00–21:00) and at airport pickup points during night-time, where demand spikes but supply fails to scale.  

On the driver side, performance inconsistency is evident:  
- 63 drivers have completion rates below 60%  
- Several drivers show over 50% cancellation rates  
- Only 5 drivers achieve 100% completion and 11 drivers have zero cancellations  

These operational inefficiencies result in:  
- Poor customer experience (long wait times, unfulfilled rides)  
- Underutilization of available drivers  
- Revenue leakage due to unmet demand  
